content: Poorly adapted to Android devices.
This app sucks. Wish i could get my money back! Doesn't even deserve one star!
Not at all like the apple one. Nothing special at all.. No sweetened tuning. Complete waste of money.
Great app

Not bad, used for tuning a pedal harp on Sony Xperia x compact. Gives good results on the gut strings but won't lock accurately to the wound steel strings in the bottom 1.5 octaves. Does a good job on the top most strings when switched to manual rather than auto. The main issue is when changing the note when in manual, it takes 4 or 5 taps to moe to the next string, which is a problem when there are 47 strings to tune, a simple note up and down arrow would make the world of difference.
No BFTS - which is why I downloaded it. Can't upgrade to the 2.0 version - it does not have that option
replyContent: Thank you for your reply. The 2.0 release is strictly designed for desktop machines. They are different products in terms of feature sets.

content: 0.1 cent in an android app. Great!

After download, the app let me know it wasn't optimized for newer versions of Android. Indeed the display was annoyingly glitchy. The app also lacks the "sweetened" tunings Peterson touts. I wanted to like this, but I ended up uninstalling.
I really really really need the sweetened tuning for Android Galaxy S7. Other than that this is pretty good.
It wouldn't open. It said it was made to work with an older version of android and might not work. I couldn't even check because it wouldn't open.
Results fade from the screen rapidly. Not as visual as needle and numbered scale.
No updates for 5 years and you're still selling this? Doesn't work very well, don't buy this app.
Needs a more current update, its jittery.
Great tuner! Certainly better than any of the others I've tried. With the inexpensive input cable it works like the $200 pedal version.
Able to hear my low B string on my 5 string Bass
Looks great. But just wouldn't work on my version of Android

I recommend this app because Peterson is the gold standard of tuners. I do, however, hope Peterson gets the memo that we Android users want our sweetened tunings like iOS users get with this app. Four stars for an extremely accurate strobe-style tuner on my phone, docked one for the lack of sweeteners.
Needs updated.. Great app but we need an Android 10 versiin.version..
No Sweetened Tunings available for android! Sweetened Tunings are only available for iPhones and iPads : (
Sluggish, unresponsive on Galaxy Note
Been using petersons since the 70's. Now I don't leave home without it.
Four year old application clearly needs some love from it's developer
Simply awesome app.
Good
Easy to use. Tuner always with phone. Remembered I had paid during phone upgrade [Google play & Android].
Last updated...2015...ummmm...?
Hasn't been updated since 2015 but still working on Pixel 3 XL. When's the next update?
dang it. thought this would have improved, over the years, for Android (galaxy s8.) it has not (at least for me) - sluggish and unresponsive /iOS version rocks, though!
does not read pitches very well. my free tuner app works much better. Not worth the money. I contacted them about a refund and they passed the buck to apple.
UPDATED: Fastest tuner on my phone, easiest to tune quickly, at least on guitar, I dont use anything else anymore. Using on Android 9 (P30 Pro).
missing a lot of features and is really unusable

Was hoping this would be the same as the iPhone version, but it's lacking a lot of features for being roughly the same price. can't quickly set your base frequency, have to use their preselected colour schemes (I prefer black and white for high contrast), and doesn't have most of the other user options available.
I use this app as an alternative when I'm unable to use my Peterson strobe tuner.
Have been using it for so many years

the layout was really good and it certainly averaged a lot better but after getting my guitar to where this tuner said it was flawlessly in tune, it respectively was not. My guitar is also set up properly and properly maintained with new strings and going back through and checking everything it also said it was still in tune but despite that the instrument was clearly not in tune

NO SWEETENED TUNINGS AVAILABLE I'd give this 5 Stars if, at a minimum, the ACU Sweetener for standard was offered. It would make tuning much faster if I didn't have to think about the offset for each string. I'd love sweeteners for my alternate tunings as well. My pedal steel player doesn't believe me about how nice this is - and rightly so! Otherwise, there is no better tuner for Android. Period.
very dependant to quality of your phone mic but if you pop your phone on the speaker enclosure it will do the job just fine

very little options for android OS, I read that I could get my money back within 2 hours of purchase but after paying and downloading the app, I could no longer find the option to get my money back. As an industry standard in guitar tuning, Peterson really fell short with this app.

Extremely accurate and amazing tuner! I use this as a backup to my other Peterson tuners (clip on as well as pedal) Peterson tuners are the gold standard. So this app deserves to be 5 stars right?  Noooo!  One reason: no sweetened tunings! Sweetened tunings are a must! The iOS version has them, without this then this is just another ho-hum tuning app.  That's why I'm rating it so low.  Peterson, there are way more people using Android than iOS, why would you write us off?

$10 for a tuner that you can get for free anywhere. The upside would have been the add-ons that you can get for the iPhone version that aren't available for the Android version. One star until that is fixed, otherwise, it's just another tuner.
Peterson has been in the strobe business for years. Their products a simply best!
Amazing app! Very visual so you don't need to be looking at it closely

This app really needs an update. It's way overpriced on android for what it 
is. The iOS version works seamlessly and looks great, but this is really 
not the case with the android version. Would not recommend anyone to 
purchase it until it's been given a proper update.

I dont play pedal steel or need sweetened tunings, just need a great, 
accurate tuner for my electrics, occasionally for adjusting intonation. The 
functionality is there, but it's slow and the graphics look very rough 
compared to the iOS version of istrobosoft. Anyone can compare them and 
immediately see the huge difference in quality. We paid the same price as 
iOS users, where is the quality, Peterson?
Very disappointed. Not even close to the iOS version, no noise reduction.
This is most accurate.

I find the app simple and accurate. I use it for pedal steel but I don't attempt "sweetened" or otherwise offset tunings. This tuner will not automate that process. There is a cable available from Peterson's website that lets me plug direct in to my phone; I use it on gigs & in noisy environments with no problem.

Would be average if it were free...for $10, forget about it. None of the ios features, really seems like a fleecing.  Peterson, you're better than this...make it "The Best" or don't put your name on it.
No promised sweetened tunings. $10 wasted.
Work great with strings instrument
What T F - I replace my phone with a same model and I cannot download this app - why? Well Peterson has no idea. How about Google- what what you don't know either !
Tuner is all over the place, play a note and within a fraction of a second it has told you that you are flat,sharp and in tune, feel like I've been royally ripped off
It's not terrible, but we were told we'd get sweetened tunings over a year ago. What's the deal, Peterson? $10 for nothing. I guess I'll stick with the amazing ClearTune.
No sirve para afinar pianos, no capta frecuencias altas ni bajas .

What a huge disappointment. No way to enter offsets.  I am a pedal steel player, and we have offsets needed to accurately tune.  That is built in to most of their tuners.  The iPhone app has sweetened tunings that you can buy to give you offsets that we need.  Petersen has obviously decided that Android users are not important enough to make this feature available to us.  I use a Stroboflip right now, but it would be nice to use my phone.  This app can work if you have a chart of your offsets, or memorize them.  A decent app, but too much work for a pedal steel player.
guys, this needs to have temperament options like the iOS version. its the same price, makes no sense!

Website says it has sweetened tunings available...which was the ONLY reason I spent 9.99 on the app. The Droid app does NOT even offer a way to get them. Wanted to use it for the "James Taylor" acoustic tuning...before spending $140+ to get the desktop stroboplus hd...well...
I have always wanted a reliable, readily available pocket strobe. No need to look further.
Lacks features of iOS version. I wish I hadn't  purchased this. After switching to Android from an iPhone 6 I expected the same features and performance. Not even close. I feel robbed.

Misleading!  The website says the app has 89 available sweetened tunings. Only way farther on the page does it mention they are only for IOS and in-app purchases. The Android app does the same or less than other free tuning apps.
Much more accurate, and correspondingly more difficult to use.  But once you learn how, your results will be incredible.

Definitely NOT the iOS version. Extremely disappointing, as the iOS version is top notch, whilst some free tuners are better than this. Please make it like the iOS version, especially for the paid users. It's a complete ripoff, and a slap in the face to consumers when you pay for a premium app (especially one as expensive as this one) nothing changes, except for added color themes. C'mon. Be better than that. As for potential customers, I give you this warning: don't be stupid. Save your money for an app that's actually worth it. As a matter of fact, why don't you go out and get some fries and a coke from McDonald's. You're money would be better spent anywhere else but here.

When I first bought this and downloaded this the adapter cable worked so I could plug into my android phone.  Now that no longer works and it's not the cord. The program has a newer version but it will not update itself either and I have tried several ways. I am disappointed with this app but I love their tuner pedals and strobe flip as I own 4 of them. This app needs some help to be worth the $10.00 I paid to download it.
Very useful for my music demands.
A superb app, quick, easy and accurate. Thank you!

Got this app for bagpipe tuning because a friend had the SAME APP for iphone, but for some strange reason the iPhone version has MUCH MUCH MORE options  (i.e. Bagpipe tuning settings). I'm sure it's great on iPhone but DO NOT DO NOT DO NOT spend any money on this pathetic app for Android. ...And may the force be with us all

I have a Peterson Strobo-clip and this package is every bit as accurate. If you read the manual and take the time to understand what it is telling you you should in no way have an issue...  This is a really handy item to carry with you without the excess bulk of a tuner. I can't  say enough good about the whole matter...

I build percussion instruments with short sustain.  I got this app on an old iPhone 4 when I was building some marimba keys. Worked better than any other app I tried. I recently had another similar build, but now have a galaxy s5.  I tried some free tuners with no luck so decided to buy this again but for Android. Not nearly the options or features of iOS version. It wouldn't register the keys to tune them. I pulled out my old iPhone and ran them side by side... iPhone registered every hit on the key.
Awesome tuner app. Easy to use and extremely accurate. I'm a professional guitarist and writer and I strongly recommend this app. ðŸŽ¸ðŸ˜ŽðŸŽ¸
Great app... does what it says on the tin. Used on a HTC One M8

Switched to Android from iOS recently. This app is great on IOS but completely useless for Android. It lacks critical settings such as input level and noise reduction. The frame rate is also so slow that it's impossible to tune. I ended up with my guitar less in tune than before I started. Refund after only 5 minutes.
Seemingly behind compared to iOS version.
I would give it a 0. Way overpriced, doesn't even work. I wish I could have a refund. I recommend pitch lab pro, which is free and works very good.

I had this for my old iPhone and it worked better than any other tuner. I used it to set up my guitars and basses and it was always spot on accurate and easy to use. When I switched to the Android platform I bought the application again hoping for similar performance. I was sorely disappointed; even the free tuner apps work better than this. The updates have helped slightly, but not enough to make it useful.
Mic works okay, but works better w/ clip-on piezo ($17).

I realize that it must be more difficult to optimize an app for Android where hardware specs are more varied, but this app isn't nearly as smooth as the iOS version. Tuning accuracy is still unmatched in my experience.
Use this app in my pre-show warm up and writing sessions. Very reliable for guitar, horns, and vocals

Peterson is a great tuner on iOS, but here the lag is too much to deal with.  I prefer Android over iOS, but not in this case.  Luckily I have an old iPhone I keep around just for the Peterson strobe tuner

I really like this tuning app because of it's accuracy and the aesthetics, but I wish there was some way to adjust the microphone settings on my phone (1st gen Moto X) through the app because right now the tuning app is barely registering any sound coming from my instrument. It seemed like my friend's iPhone was a lot more sensitive to sound - not sure if that was because of the app or device.   I even purchased the adaptor cable hoping to use it with a pickup mic, but it doesn't seem to be working... I read reviews of the adaptor saying that it worked with android devices, and I thought it would work with my phone as well.
This app has been trying to download for three days, the Payment has been drawn from my account, any help would be appreciated

TOTALLY out of tune. I have the REAL Peterson tuner in my studio. This app is completely off. I have no idea what they did but the calibration is garbage. Awful. I've seen people complaining about the smoothness... no problem there. Works fine. Hears the guitar no problem. Just not in tune. So off. I have a Samsung Note 3.
Outstanding accuracy and ease of use. I could not be happier.
I had good hopes, but no. Animation is not smooth, had problems tracking notes on my bass. Used a direct connection, so no mic issues.
Jumps all ovee the place on my Galaxy S5. Completely useless as far as I can tell.

Sadly, this app has very basic functionality.  If you need "spot-on" accuracy, this is not for you.  Contacting customer support,  got me a "you'll need to buy  Strobosoft" recommendation ($134). I'm really disappointed with this app.
Great app! Worth every dime
Very accurate
I have been a fan for a long time!

I Iove my Strobostomp, this obviously isn't going to replace that, and it won't be as useful as a clip on in noisy situations. This probably isn't as good as the iOS version either. But it works well on both my GS2 and GS3 and I'm happy with it.

...which has the same "sweetened" tuning offsets as the pedal version (which I own two of...)  For $10, you'd think you could at least manage to have them available, even if they're an add-on purchase.  Works OK otherwise - seems a little "jumpier" than the hardware version when run on my Galaxy S3. Oh, and it doesn't work well with the mic, so I popped for the cable for $12. I'm now halfway to a used pedal, or 1/3 of the way to one of the clip-ons!  Only three stars.

To put it mildly this POS software is a rip off and works very poorly if at all. I don't know how it could have gotten so many good reviews for something so awful. This software needs a lot of work. I would give it a 0 star rating if I could. Lets hope there is an update that works real soon.
Multiple ios users recommended this to me, but there seems to be no support for the subpar Android version. Bring this one up to the same level as the iPhone version and it'll be perfect.

I really like this app. Its become really handy! I would like this app to update and be more like the IOS version though :( . Also is there a way to turn up the sensitivity? I use my normal phone mic.
I just wish I could change the temperament...

I'm an authorized Buzz Feiten Tuning System retrofitter I would pay more for a version which allows me to work with BFTS. I have the Strobo Flip and the Strobo Soft in my shop. By the way, It runs perfectly smooth in my Motorola X.
It is crap does not work well at all even if other apps are not open. I want a refund. Galexy s5

The app is OK had it on my ios and seemed to work better on pick up.  There was a boost mic button that worked better with ios. I would never go back to a iPhone after using a Droid.  It runs smoothly on a S4 but mic boost would help not working well with internal. Mic needs a dB boost button.
I am happy with this tuner, which my guitar teacher recommended. I purchased it for both my Mac and android devices. I am a singer and guitarist.

Peterson customer service sucks! I paid $99.99 for the computer software and the $9.99 for the android app only to find out that it wouldn't work on laptop as advertised without buying a midi interface for $150 and then it still didn't work right and the app couldn't even isolate the guitar's sound to tune it. I have tried several times to contact Peterson with no response. So don't buy if you are looking for support or a refund for something that does not work as advertised.

If you're serious about your tuning you need a Peterson STROBE tuner. Great if you always carry your phone and/or you forget your strobe at home. Just wish it wasn't so expensive considering it's a simulation of the strobe its really close but it might be closer to 1 cent accuracy like most chromatic tuners than the 0.1 accuracy of a physical strobe unit IMO

I have used the Iphone version of this app for years and it's beautiful. On Android (Note 3) it is jumpy, the strobe is not smooth at all.  I have started using other FREE apps that work better!. Come on Petersen! For $10 it should work right!!!! How do I get a refund.  I had it on a Samsung Note 3 and now on a MotoX. Same thing. It seems to not really hear the guitar, even amplified. The little level meter barely moves.
replyContent:
Hi Rick,

This app should give you a very smooth display.  

How many other apps are running at the same time?  

What type phone do you have?

The Android platform has a wide variety of different phones.  This app was tested with most and worked very well.

I will help to get the results you expect.

Please contact me pjb@petersontuners.com 

Pat

content: Still accurate but not nearly as fluid and smooth as iOS version. Needs improvement. Not worth $10 at the moment until strobe animation is fixed.
replyContent:
Hi Marco,

I am sorry you are experiencing problems, it is certainly not normal. 

Can you tell me how many other apps are running at the same time as the iStroboSoft?

What instrument are you tuning?  

Are you using the microphone on the phone or an external input jack of some sort?


Thanks,

Pat Bovenizer

content: Jumps around just like a cheap electronic tuner.. A proper strobe is smooth and is capable of showing multiple notes simultaneously - even software based strobes! Have a look at another popular free strobe on Playstore so see what I mean..
replyContent:
Hi Algernon,

It should not jump around like you describe.

What type phone are you using?

What instrument are you tuning?

Are there many other apps running at the same time?

Please contact me pjb@petersontuners.com

Pat

content: Kind of scary that a $10 app is almost as accurate as my $200 Peterson VSAM that I use professionally. I tuned with both side to side to see if the app was worth $10, and it definitely is.

Tuner itself is 5 stars... When  you go to make an in app  purchase for a mic jack/ guitar cable interface, it says $12.99.  When you click on the buy now it magically becomes $13.95, and you can't adjust the size of the page or text - Painfully difficult to read....almost abandoned.  When I got to checkout page, default and cheapest shipp. Was $10 for UPS Ground. For a 2 oz cable at most? What a joke, from 12.95, $1 instant markup on the next page supposedly to 24.00 Peterson shouldn't yank their customers
replyContent:
Hi Mike,

I am sorry for the trouble you had purchasing the iCable.  Please contact me so I can try to satisfy you regarding that transaction.  

pjb@petersontuners.com

Pat

content: Seriously, awesome tuner. I can't recommend this tuner enough. Sure it's 9.99, it's absolutely worth it and Peterson are worth supporting. I only wish they would allow the option of no splash screen. I shouldn't have to wait for my 10 dollar app to open with a splash screen every time I open it. It's a little irritating.
Works awesome.  Simple to use and accurate. Don't waste your time with other cheap tuners. Spend a little $.
Available at last on Android.  Fast stable and accurate.

love this on the ipad for tuning the piano/gtr - been dying for android.  I miss the 'noise filter' function; wish I could see cents AND freq without toggling; News text is too large; main font/note seems fuzzy; doesn't run as smooth vs ipad;  all this being said... THANK YOU!!!  LG g2, sprint
replyContent:
Hi Jim,

Thanks for the kind words about the app.  The noise filter feature in not possible on the Android platform like it is on the iOS.  

Try to not have too many other apps running at the same time as the iStroboSoft, that will generally make the display just as smooth as you were accustom to.

Pat

content: I've been a professional stringed instrument repair luthier for over 20 years. For the past 8 years, I've been using a Peterson model 420 mechanical strobe tuner on my workbench for fine tuning the intonation of fretted instruments and tap tuning banjo heads.  The new iStrobosoft tuner is equally accurate and easier to use due to its auto note-finding feature.  It also works well for just tuning up. Highly recommended.
